(219, 11, 'James Ambler', 'Surreal Room 1', '42 x 30cm, Pencil', 'I took inspiration for my artwork from a book called "The Rabbits" which was illustrated by Shaun Tan and it is about how England \r\n invaded Australia and there is an industrial scene with the type of buildings you see in the middle of my picture.', 'surreal-room-1.jpg', NULL),
(220, 11, 'James Murphy', 'Urban', '75 x 60cm, Acrylic', 'This piece reflects a surreal technique on reflecting the urban city and its buildings (the castle and the chaos (the riot) and much more. \r\n The background was created with acrylic paint being smeared neatly with a squeegee.', 'urban.jpg', 2),
(221, 11, 'Jack Agate', 'Surreal Room 2', '42 x 30cm, Pencil', ' A surreal room was the final piece for my project. It shows a contrast down the central line between good and evil or dark and light, \r\n but all of this is placed into a regular room. Inspiration was taken from different photographs and paintings by other Surreal artists.', 'surreal-room-2.jpg', NULL),
(222, 11, 'Jason Huang', 'Surreal Room 3', '42 x 30cm, Pencil', ' Originally my plan for my final piece was a surreal landscape but realised that it was not interesting enough, so I decided to change \r\n it into a surreal room and have part of my surreal landscape on one of the walls.', 'surreal-room-3.jpg', NULL),
(223, 11, 'Luke Alben', 'Surreal Landscape', '42 x 30cm, Coloured Pencil', 'Surreal landscape influenced by the artists Salvador Dali and Rene Magritte.', 'surreal-landscape.jpg', NULL),
(224, 11, 'James Parker', 'The Man with the Missing Eye', '42 x 30cm, Watercolour and Pencil', 'My painting is called "The man with the missing eye". Rene Magritte inspired me to do this piece of art by the way he used everyday \r\n objects into different situations that could have loads of different, wacky meanings', 'the-man-with.jpg', 3),
(225, 11, 'Matthew Hindley', 'Surreal Room 4', '42 x 30cm, Coloured Pencil', 'For my landscape I was inspired by Rene Magritte and weird ideas of a landscape. From throwing up unicorns to bleeding eyes that float. \r\n The railway aspect of it all came from the artist Dali, also the windmills with butterfly wings came from the artist Vladimir Kush.', 'surreal-landscape-4.jpg', NULL),
(226, 11, 'Jonathan Burrows', 'Surreal Room 5', '42 x 30cm, Pencil', 'This piece was inspired by Dali and Magritte; it makes you think outside the box. I included things which are not normal, \r\n the track going into the distance has a good affect as well as the river under it, the fish going into the scissors then \r\n get cut in half and bleed, adding to the effect.', 'surreal-room-5.jpg', NULL),
(227, 11, 'Ben Foster', 'Continuous Line', '23 x 18cm, Wire', 'This piece was inspired by the artist Cathy miles. I have used one continuous piece of wire to form the shape, adding finer \r\ncoloured wire for the detail.', 'continuous-line.jpg', 1),
(228, 11, 'Callum McKenna', 'My City 1', '21 x 29cm, Pencil', 'The piece of work that I am entering is inspired by Hundertwasser. This sketchbook page was the original idea that \r\n I had for a T shirt design that came from the project "My City"', 'my-city-1.jpg', NULL),
(229, 11, 'Bassam Abdullah', 'My City 2', '21 x 29cm, Digital Image', 'This was my final design for a project ‘My city’ I was inspired by the Artist Hundertwasser. \r\n I scanned in drawings from my sketchbook and using the program Photoshop layered them together and used different effects.', 'my-city-2.jpg', NULL),
(230, 11, 'Jamie Samuel', 'The Lone Balloonist', '21 x 58cm, Pencil', 'This is a series of pages I designed for a surreal book. I was inspired by the children''s books by Colin Thompson.', 'the-lone-balloonist.jpg', NULL),
(231, 11, 'Isaac Sims', 'Surreal Room 6', '42 x 30cm, Pencil and Watercolour', 'This is my surreal room inspired by Magritte and Dali.', 'surreal-room-6.jpg', NULL),
(232, 11, 'Thomas Durban', 'Maybe When You''re Older', '21 x 29cm, Pencil and Pen', 'This was a surreal image that was influenced by Pop art.', 'maybe-when-youre.jpg', NULL),
(233, 11, 'Adam Gilboy', 'Surreal Box', '42 x 30cm, Coloured Pencil', 'For my surreal piece, I created a cube with different ideas all cramped into a few small boxes. \r\n I was influenced by Surreal artists such as Rene Magritte, who is famous for his Surrealism.', 'surreal-box.jpg', NULL),
